It is possible to mix 2 or more different types of data </br>
as long as they are <b>they are compatible with each other</b> </br> </br>

Ex. </br>
short and long, both are numeric types </br>
char, byte, short --> promoted to int </br>
if one operand is a long --> long </br>
float </br>
double </br></br>

</br>
Promotions apply only to the values operated upon when an expression is evaluated. </br>
Type promotion only affects the evaluation of an expression.
